Description: Gorgeous purple PRS SE Torero with Floyd Rose bridge, neck-through body construction and PRS SE gig bag; the whammy bar is included. Guitar is in really good shape. Didn’t notice any dings, dents or anything like that. You know the info on Toreros. They’re “a shredder’s dream” says Mr. PRS himself. But here’s some details: mahogany body with flame-maple veneer, 25 1/2” scale length, jumbo frets, master volume and tone, 3-way blade switch, standard PRS tuners and standard strap buttons. I put on the cool PRS truss rod cover. It came with a blank one. Kept in smoke-free home, no pets and in the gig bag most of the time. Played it maybe five times. I bought this on eBay back in April and just haven’t played it. And I’m not a shredder. Haven’t played many of my guitars, to be honest. The former owner switched out the EMG pickups for the Bare Knuckle Black Hawk pickups in white. He got rid of the EMGs so I don’t have them. See address of link below for more intel on the pups... https://www.bareknucklepickups.co.uk/pickup/humbucker/black-hawk The pickups are pricey, they’re an upgrade. I found a white one online and it was $170 for just the bridge pickup. Upwards of $290 for a pair. So it’s a great, good looking guitar but I just don’t play it enough and could use the money. Good luck bidding!!
Title: PRS SE Torero, Purple w/ Bare Knuckle Black Hawk Pickups
